Pollen hosts. Oligolectic on Fabaceae (Tab. 1; Popov 1960 ; Özbek 1979 , 2013 ; Özbek & Zanden 1992 ); pollen hosts are species of Galegeae (e.g.
Astragalus
), Genisteae, Hedysareae (e.g.
Onobrychis
), Loteae (e.g.
Lotus
), Trifolieae (e.g.
Medicago
,
Trifolium
) and other Fabaceae tribes. The larval provision of one brood cell from Iran exlusively consisted of pollen of
Astragalus
.
